                     <origDate when="1699">The colophon states that the Ms. was
                        completed during the time of King ʾIyāsu and Metropolitan Mārqos, probably
                        King ʾIyāsu I (r. 1682-1706) and ʾabuna Mārqos IV (in tenure from 1698) (cp.
                        EAE III, 250a).</origDate>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>Za-Walda Māryām is mentioned as the
                     commissioner of the Ms. in the subscriptio on <locus target="#208r">208r</locus> and in some supplication formulas (e.g., <locus target="#160va">160va</locus>, 160vb, 161rc, 162rc, 183rc, 197rc, 197va) in
                     the final part of the Ms. In the supplication on <locus target="#160va">160va</locus>, he is mentioned together with "the children of this church"
                     (daqiqa zatti beta krǝstiyān).&#xD; Some personal names are written over
                     erasures in a secondary hand in the supplication formulas throughout the Ms.,
                     most probably to replace the original names of the donors: Tasfā Māryām (e.g.,
                     <locus target="#4vb">4vb</locus>, 7rb, 7va, 12rb), Za-Manfas Qǝddus (e.g.,
                     <locus target="#7vb">7vb</locus>, 17ra, 29vb), Walatta ʾAqlesya (<locus target="#82vc">82vc</locus>), Walatta Ḥǝywat (e.g., <locus target="#84rc">84rc</locus>, 87rb).</provenance>
